### **OPPORTUNITY 5: Parameterized Tests with [DataTestMethod]**

**Current Problem:** Similar test structures with different inputs (lines 8-29, 31-53, 79-97, 99-120, 122-143)

**Strategy - Combine into single parameterized test:**
```csharp
[DataTestMethod]
[DataRow("C001", "alice@example.com", 100, 2, 9.99, true, "Processed")]
[DataRow("C002", "bob@example.com", 100, 1, 9.99, true, "Processed")]
[DataRow("C004", "dave@example.com", 100, 0, 0, false, "NoItems")]
[DataRow("C005", null, 100, 1, 9.99, false, "InvalidEmail")]
[DataRow("C006", "eve@example.com", 0, 10, 9.99, false, "OutOfStock")]
public void ProcessOrder_VariousScenarios(string customerId, string email, int stockLevel, 
    int quantity, decimal price, bool expectedSuccess, string expectedStatus)
{
    var processor = new OrderProcessorBuilder().WithStockLevel(stockLevel).Build();
    var order = new OrderBuilder()
        .WithCustomerId(customerId)
        .WithEmail(email)
        .AddItem("P1", "Widget", quantity, (decimal)price)
        .Build();

    var result = processor.Process(order);

    OrderAssertions.AssertOrderResult(result, expectedSuccess, expectedStatus);
}
```

**Reduction:** Consolidates 5 test methods (lines 8-29, 31-53, 79-97, 99-120, 122-143) into 1

